Class SubscriberRow

java.lang.Object
Client.SubscriberRow
public class SubscriberRow extends Object
JavaFX row-model for displaying Subscriber data in a TableView.

This class wraps subscriber fields using JavaFX Property types so the UI can:

  • Bind table columns to properties
  • Support automatic refresh if values change (if you later add setters)
Typical usage: 
TableColumn<SubscriberRow, String> col = new TableColumn<>("Email");
col.setCellValueFactory(new PropertyValueFactory<>("email"));

  • Constructor Details

    • SubscriberRow

      public SubscriberRow(String subscriberId, String fullName, String phone, String email, String birthDate)
      Creates a new SubscriberRow instance for TableView display.
      Parameters:
      subscriberId - subscriber unique id/username
      fullName - subscriber full name
      phone - subscriber phone number
      email - subscriber email address
      birthDate - birth date formatted as a string (e.g., "2001-05-12")
